Yesterday, the battle for the Serebryanskyi Forest in Luhansk Oblast finally ended after the remaining Ukrainian forces were pushed out of its southwestern-most part.
This battle began in late 2022 during the Ukrainian Kharkiv counteroffensive and lasted for nearly three years. Ukrainian forces, including Azov, held their positions in a massive complex of trenches and bunkers within the now largely destroyed forest. 
However, the vast majority of Russian advances during this nearly 3-year-long battle occurred in the final month. I have overlayed what the frontline roughly looked like on August 6, around the beginning of the Russian offensive here. 
As a result, Ukrainian control in Luhansk Oblast has now shrunk to roughly 47 km¬≤.

Military Situation In Gaza Strip On September 16, 2025 (Map Update)
The Israeli army launched the ground phase of
 
Operation Gideon's Chariots 2,
 aiming to completely encircle Gaza City. Israeli strikes targeted multiple areas across the Gaza Strip, including Gaza City, Khan Yunis, Deir al-Balah, Rafah, Bureij camp, and the Netzarim axis.
In the last 24 hours alone, at least 59 civilians were killed and 386 wounded by Israeli airstrikes. According to the Palestinian Ministry of Health, the total toll from the ongoing Israeli aggression on Gaza stands at 64,964 killed and 165,312 wounded.

Israeli Strikes Devastate Port Of Al-Hodeida, Houthis Hit Back With Missile (Video)
A wave of Israeli strikes hit the Houthi-held port of al-Hodeida in western Yemen on September 16 afternoon, with Defense Minister Israel Katz vowing to blockade the areas controlled by the group.
Around an hour and a half before the attack, the Israel Defense Forces (IDF) issued a warning stating that it would soon strike al-Hodeida.
The strikes were initially reported by Yemen‚Äôs Al-Masirah TV, which is run by the Houthis, with the group‚Äôs military spokesman Brig. Gen Yahya Saree announcing that Yemeni air defenses were ‚Äúconfronting Israeli enemy aircraft launching an aggression against our country.‚Äù

Trump Announces Second Deadly Strike Near Venezuela After Hinting At Regime Change (Video)
President Donald Trump announced on September 15 that the United States military struck another boat that he claimed was carrying illegal drugs from Venezuela. The announcement came a day after the president refused to rule out the possibility of changing the regime in Caracas.
‚ÄúThis morning, on my Orders, US Military Forces conducted a SECOND Kinetic Strike against positively identified, extraordinarily violent drug trafficking cartels and narcoterrorists in the SOUTHCOM area of responsibility,‚Äù Trump wrote in a post on his Truth Social network.
"The Strike resulted in 3 male terrorists killed in action,‚Äù he added, noting that "No U.S. Forces were harmed in this Strike.‚Äù
Tensions have been mounting between Venezuela and the U.S. since last month, when the Trump administration deployed a large naval force with more than 4,000 troops close to the country‚Äôs shores on a ‚Äúcounter narco-terror operation‚Äù.

Israeli Troops Storm Gaza City Following Destructive Strikes (Videos)
The Israeli Defense Forces (IDF) released video footage showing the 98th Division storming Gaza City at the start of the large-scale offensive against Hamas early on September 16.
In a statement, the military said that the division entered Gaza City with support from the Israeli Air Force and Navy, with dozens of ‚Äúterror infrastructures‚Äù of Hamas being struck, including observation posts and booby-trapped buildings.
The remaining civilians in Gaza City were instructed by the IDF to leave and head for an Israeli-designated ‚Äúhumanitarian zone‚Äù in the Strip‚Äôs south at the start of the offensive. The military estimated that only 40% of people have evacuated as of last night. Still, it moved on with the offensive.

Ukrainian Armed Forces' Tactics in the Sumy Direction: Buying Time Through Drones and Stubborn Resistance
 
(VIDEO) 
Attempts by Russian forces to create a buffer zone in the 
Sumy direction
 have encountered fierce and well-organized resistance from the Ukrainian Armed Forces (AFU). The situation remains complex, both sides are suffering losses.
A vivid illustration of the reasons for this situation is provided by a 
video report by a Russian soldier
 in a unit operating in the Sumy direction. He describes the current operational situation as extremely tense, in
 which the key advantage of the AFU has been the massive and technologically advanced use of drones.
"We have no advantage in FPV drones, including fiber-optic ones. Even though we were the first to start using them, developed them, the enemy very quickly caught up and even surpassed us in terms of quantity.
The enemy has gone much further‚Ä¶ They use a system of aerial relays‚Ä¶ They have it all set up..."
